  "text": "In this paper, we present solid random-phase Gabor noise, a new noise function based on Gabor noise [CITATION_1] ]. Our new noise uses slicing, which preserves continuity at sharp edges ( Fig. 1(d.1) ). Since filtering is inherently a 2D operation (i.e., it depends on surface orientation) [CITATION_2] ], we have to explicitly model the slicing of the 3D Gabor kernels to be able to filter the resulting 2D Gabor kernels. This requires the introduction of a new Gabor kernel, the phase-augmented Gabor kernel, and a new Gabor noise, random-phase Gabor noise. Our new noise uses a filtering approach based on that of [CITATION_3] , which supports high-quality anisotropic filtering ( Fig. 1(d.2) ).",
